{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17597756","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17597756"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:28:51+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:28:51+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15427"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15427","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15427"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.19,0.19,0.12,0.12,0.38]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8118"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66751"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8118","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8118"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15427"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52205"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8760"},{"type":"tags","id":"10956"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19685"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19689"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22307"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66751","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66751"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA histological section from a gallbladder biopsy of a patient with chronic cholecystitis is shown (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following histological features is most likely to be visible in this specimen?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Fibrous tissue","Granulomatous inflammation","Mononuclear cell infiltrate","Neutrophilic infiltrate","Rokitansky-Aschoff sinuses"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn chronic cholecystitis, several characteristic histological features are typically present. \u003Cstrong\u003EFibrous tissue\u003C/strong\u003E may develop as part of the chronic inflammatory process. A \u003Cstrong\u003Emononuclear cell infiltrate\u003C/strong\u003E consisting of lymphocytes and plasma cells is commonly seen, rather than a \u003Cstrong\u003Eneutrophilic infiltrate\u003C/strong\u003E which is more characteristic of acute inflammation. \u003Cstrong\u003EGranulomatous inflammation\u003C/strong\u003E is not typically associated with chronic cholecystitis.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe most characteristic finding is the presence of \u003Cstrong\u003ERokitansky-Aschoff sinuses\u003C/strong\u003E, which are epithelium-lined invaginations extending into the gallbladder wall. These develop as a result of increased intraluminal pressure and are considered a diagnostic feature of chronic cholecystitis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Chronic cholecystitis shows characteristic Rokitansky-Aschoff sinuses on histology, which are epithelium-lined invaginations into the gallbladder wall.","Chronic inflammation of the gallbladder is characterised by mononuclear cell infiltration and fibrosis.","Rokitansky-Aschoff sinuses develop due to increased intraluminal pressure in the gallbladder."],"references":["Cariati A, Cetta F. Rokitansky-Aschoff sinuses of the gallbladder are associated with black pigment gallstone formation: a scanning electron microscopy study. Ultrastruct Pathol. 2003 Jul-Aug;27(4):265-70. doi: 10.1080/01913120309913. PMID: 12907372.","Dorantes-Heredia R, Chabl\u00e9-Montero F, Henson DE, Albores-Saavedra J. Rokitansky-Aschoff sinuses mimicking adenocarcinoma of the gallbladder: a study of 8 cases. Am J Surg Pathol. 2013 Aug;37(8):1269-74. doi: 10.1097/PAS.0b013e318286bd39. PMID: 23715158.","Jones MW, Gnanapandithan K, Panneerselvam D, Ferguson T. Chronic Cholecystitis. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29261986.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","\u0022Rokitansky-Aschoff sinus in a case of chronic cholecystitis\u0022 by Patho is licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported license. https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Rokitansky-Aschoff_sinus_in_a_case_of_chronic_cholecystitis.JPG"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52205"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15427"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21161"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21161","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21161"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/5ohCJo7qV6WPLig04msGqrbxXgvsL6.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/5ohCJo7qV6WPLig04msGqrbxXgvsL6.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1490,"height":1144}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52205","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52205"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-01T21:10:33+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-01T21:11:00+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8118"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66751"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"ty